FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784810903
OL,3,CThames Water announces hosepipe ban
OL,4,Cfor millions of customers
OL,6,FThe restriction covers the 10.1
OL,7,Fmillion customers that the firm
OL,8,Fsupplies with water across London, the
OL,9,FThames Valley and the home counties,
OL,10,Fbut not to waste-only customers or
OL,11,Fthose supplied by another water
OL,12,Fcompany.
OL,14,FIt means people must not use hosepipes
OL,15,Ffor any non-essential activities, such
OL,16,Fas watering gardens, cleaning cars,
OL,17,Ffilling paddling pools or topping up
OL,18,Fhot tubs.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784810903
OL,3,CThames Water announces hosepipe ban
OL,4,Cfor millions of customers
OL,6,FPressure on water resources is
OL,7,Fintensifying, with the current warm
OL,8,Fconditions following three
OL,9,Funprecedented heatwaves and the driest
OL,10,Fspring on record for England and Wales.
OL,12,FThe Environment Agency revealed on
OL,13,FTuesday that large parts of southern,
OL,14,Fcentral and eastern England have moved
OL,15,Fcloser to official drought status.
OL,17,FThames Water becomes the latest in a
OL,18,Fstring of hosepipe bans already
OL,19,Fannounced across southern England,
OL,20,Fwhich has seen very little rainfall
OL,21,Fthis month.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784810903
OL,3,CThames Water announces hosepipe ban
OL,4,Cfor millions of customers
OL,6,FThe company said water use is
OL,7,Fcurrently 10% above normal in the
OL,8,FThames Valley and the Home Counties,
OL,9,Fas well as 7% above normal in London.
OL,11,FCustomers are currently using an extra
OL,12,F100 million litres every day `
OL,13,Fequivalent to adding all the homes in
OL,14,FManchester to the network, the firm
OL,15,Fadded.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784810903
OL,3,CThames Water announces hosepipe ban
OL,4,Cfor millions of customers
OL,6,FPeriods of hot weather can push up
OL,7,Fdemand as people consume more water to
OL,8,Fstay cool and water gardens, while
OL,9,Ffarmers use more for crop irrigation
OL,10,Fand industries use more for protecting
OL,11,Finfrastructure from the heat.
OL,13,FHotter temperatures can also lead to
OL,14,Fphysical pressure on underground water
OL,15,Fpipes, leading to higher rates or
OL,16,Fbursts and leaks, while the lack of
OL,17,Frainfall means very little
OL,18,Freplenishment for reservoirs.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784810903
OL,3,CThames Water announces hosepipe ban
OL,4,Cfor millions of customers
OL,6,FThe water firm said it will keep the
OL,7,Fsituation under review and lift
OL,8,Frestrictions as soon as it is safe to
OL,9,Fdo so.
OL,11,FNevil Muncaster, director of strategic
OL,12,Fwater resources at Thames Water, said:
OL,13,F"We would not be taking this step
OL,14,Funless it was necessary to protect
OL,15,Fwater supplies for everyone and the
OL,16,Fenvironment.
OL,18,F"While there is enough water for
OL,19,Fessential use, we need to reduce non-
OL,20,Fessential outdoor demand to keep taps
OL,21,Fflowing.
OL,26,@uD@AOUzD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784810903
OL,3,CThames Water announces hosepipe ban
OL,4,Cfor millions of customers
OL,6,F"Many customers have already reduced
OL,7,Ftheir water use and that support has
OL,8,Fmade a difference. Thank you to
OL,9,Feveryone who has already changed their
OL,10,Fdaily habits."
OL,12,FMr Muncaster added that Thames Water
OL,13,Fteams are working around the clock to
OL,14,Fkeep water moving, fix leaks and
OL,15,Fsupport customers.
OL,17,FThe Thames Water region received only
OL,18,F40% of average rainfall this spring,
OL,19,Ffollowed by periods of exceptionally
OL,20,Fhot weather, the firm said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@NO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784810903
OL,3,CThames Water announces hosepipe ban
OL,4,Cfor millions of customers
OL,6,FWhile Thames Water plans for periods
OL,7,Fof dry weather and increased summer
OL,8,Fdemand, it said the scale and duration
OL,9,Fof recent demand is having a
OL,10,F"significant impact" on water
OL,11,Fresources.
OL,13,FBans are also in place for Southern
OL,14,FWater customers in Hampshire and the
OL,15,FIsle of Wight, Cambridge Water
OL,16,Fcustomers, Affinity Water customers in
OL,17,FBedfordshire, Berkshire,
OL,18,FBuckinghamshire, Essex, Hertfordshire,
OL,19,FSurrey and parts of London, and
OL,20,FAnglian Water customers in the East of
OL,21,FEngland.
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@TO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784810903
OL,3,CThames Water announces hosepipe ban
OL,4,Cfor millions of customers
OL,6,FOn Monday, South East Water also
OL,7,Fannounced that 2.4 million customers
OL,8,Fwill be affected by temporary
OL,9,Frestrictions in Sussex, Surrey,
OL,10,FHampshire and Berkshire from Saturday,
OL,11,Fcoming on top of a ban it already put
OL,12,Fin place for areas of Kent.
OL,14,FSevern Trent, Essex and Suffolk Water,
OL,15,FWessex Water and Portsmouth Water have
OL,16,Falso urged customers to use water
OL,17,Fwisely amid the heatwave.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784810903
OL,3,CThames Water announces hosepipe ban
OL,4,Cfor millions of customers
OL,6,FThe Environment Agency said six
OL,7,Freservoirs are currently classed as
OL,8,Fhaving "notably low" levels, including
OL,9,FWimbleball in Somerset, Grafham in
OL,10,FCambridgeshire and Hanningfield in
OL,11,FEssex, while Blagdon reservoir in
OL,12,FSomerset is classed as being
OL,13,F"exceptionally low".
OL,15,FMeanwhile, only 13% of rivers are
OL,16,Fclassed at normal levels for this time
OL,17,Fof year, with the Rivers Avon
OL,18,F(Hampshire), Cam, Derwent (Yorkshire),
OL,19,FSwale, Tone, Wye and Yare currently
OL,20,Fseeing exceptionally low levels.
OL,26,@pD@HOUpD@TO]uD@AOUuD@SO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G10/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,385,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F384A1784810903
OL,3,CThames Water announces hosepipe ban
OL,4,Cfor millions of customers
OL,6,FHelen Wakeham, chair of the National
OL,7,FDrought Group and director of water at
OL,8,Fthe Environment Agency, said: "All
OL,9,Fsectors are taking action, and we are
OL,10,Fgrateful to the public for following
OL,11,Fthe restrictions, where in place, to
OL,12,Fmake sure there is enough water for
OL,13,Feveryone this summer.
OL,15,F"We want everyone to stay safe and
OL,16,Fhydrated during the hot weather but
OL,17,Fevery drop we can save is a drop more
OL,18,Ffor nature and agriculture."
OL,26,@pD@_OUwD@AOUzD@\O]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
